me and violence, and resolve relationship problems. But can people simply decide to believe in a religion because of the benefits it reportedly delivers? Based on extensive fieldwork among Pentecostal men in Caracas, Venezuela, this rich urban ethnography seeks an explanation for the explosion of Evangelical Protestantism, unraveling the cultural and personal dynamics of Evangelical conversion to show how and why these men make the choice to convert, and how they come to have faith in a new system of beliefs and practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianity and culturezVenezuelazCaracas. 0aEvangelicalismzVenezuelazCaracas. 0aMenxReligious life. 0aPentecostalismzVenezuelazCaracasvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  abenefits of religion.  acaracas.  achristian converts.  achristianity.  aconflict resolution.  acultural agency.  acultural history.  aethnographers.  aevangelical conversion.  aevangelical protestantism.  aevangelicalism.  afaith and religion.  afieldwork.  alatin american history.  alatin american studies.  anonfiction.  aovercoming substance abuse.  apentecostal men.  areligious communities.  areligious historians.  aself discipline.  asouth america.  aurban ethnography.  avenezuela.  aworld religions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024942440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094014740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940147/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY